The 'men's 100 m freestyle' at the 2009 World Championships took place on 29
July (heats and semifinals) and the evening of 30 July (finals) at the Foro
Italico in Rome, Italy.

Existing records at the start of the 2009 Championships were: *World record
(WR): 47.05, Eamon Sullivan (Australia), 13 August 2008, Beijing, China
*Championship record (CR): 48.12, Filippo Magnini (Italy), Montreal 2005,
(28 July 2005)
